    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">After gathering enough points you could exchange them for <strong>$real$money$ </strong>(e.g.: <strong>5000 points</strong> would be <strong>5$</strong>). Only, thereâ€™s a <strong>catch</strong>. I know, surprising right?</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In order to play a 1v1 game you would need to spend what they called â€œticketsâ€. And in order to win those said â€œticketsâ€, you would need to win games. A <strong>vicious cycle</strong> indeed. On top of that, remember what I said previously about <strong>ads</strong>? The developer still needs to eat. So, after a game is finished, you would have a very interesting ad â˜ï¸ waiting for you on the other side (with a duration of <strong>over 30 seconds </strong>most of the times and a button to close it that can only be seen through a microscope).</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Nonetheless, I didnâ€™t let that stopÂ me. Oh, no sir!</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><em>&gt; â€œThere must be a way to make at least some money from this.â€</em></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">After thinking about it for a bit and doing some calculations, I figured something out, which I will explain with the fluxogram below:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
