        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">We can select the numbers â€œ54â€ and â€œ49â€, and use the <strong>Variable Set</strong> to store the result. The cool part about the Interact block is that, it provides a tool to inspect all elements in the interface and returns the <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/XPath" target="_self">XPath</a> to the element, so that you can inspect or click it.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Finally, with the <strong>For Each </strong>block, I could iterate through the result (in this case 54 + 49 = 103) and click the buttons â€œ1â€, â€œ0â€, â€œ3â€ and â€œEnterâ€, by using the Interact block again.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
